#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:10
msgid "Private key image serves to detect double spending attempts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:13
msgid ""
"In Monero funds are always sent to a one-time public key `P`.  Related one-"
"time private key `x` is specific to unspent output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:15
msgid ""
"As output can be spent only once (in whole), the related private key can be "
"used only once as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:18
msgid ""
"Thus, specific private key image `I` being present on the blockchain means "
"that related output was already spent, and subsequent attempts must not be "
"allowed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:22
msgid ""
"This whole scheme is necessary because Monero uses Ring Signatures which "
"make it impossible to know whom exactly signed the transaction.  This is why "
"a simple Bitcoin-like double spending check wouldn't work here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid "Definition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "    I = x*Hp(P)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:28
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
msgid "`I` - private key image (or \"key image\" for short)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
msgid "`x` - one-time private key used to unlock an unspent output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
msgid "`P` - one-time public key of an unspent output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
msgid "`Hp()` - hash function accepting an EC point as an argument"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:35
msgid "The `P` comes from this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "    P = xG\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:39
msgid ""
"Where `G` is the [edwards25519](/cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519) base "
"point."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:41
msgid "Substitute `P` with `xG` and we get:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "    I = x*Hp(xG)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:45
msgid "The key image `I` is a one-way function of the private key `x`."
msgstr ""

